videos.headline: Clemson converts 3rd down with acrobatic catch
videos.description: On third-and-six, Ray-Ray McCloud adjusts in the air to make a contested grab on a pass from Kelly Bryant for a gain of 27 yards.

videos.headline: Tigers can't convert near goal line
videos.description: On third-and-goal from the Virginia Tech 6-yard line, Kelly Bryant's pass to Deon Cain is tipped away, forcing Clemson to settle for a field goal.

videos.headline: Feaster breaks free for 60-yard Clemson TD
videos.description: Kelly Bryant finds a wide-open Tavien Feaster along the right sideline, and Feaster takes it all the way to the house for a touchdown, giving Clemson an early 10-0 lead.

videos.headline: Virginia Tech gets on the board with 43-yard FG
videos.description: The Hokies score their first points of the game off of a 43-yard field goal from kicker Joey Slye,  cutting the Clemson lead to 7.

videos.headline: Fuller pounds it in for Clemson
videos.description: C.J. Fuller batters through the Virginia Tech defense to score a touchdown from one yard out, giving Clemson a 17-3 lead.

videos.headline: Clemson leads after physical half
videos.description: Tavien Feaster runs down the field for a 60-yard touchdown in the first quarter and C.J. Fuller punches it in from a yard out to give Clemson a 17-3 lead over Virginia Tech at the half.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Clemson leads after physical half) 2017/09/30

videos.headline: Fuente: VT must execute to have chance in second half
videos.description: Virginia Tech coach Justin Fuente says his team started moving the ball better at the end of the first half, but they can't afford mistakes against a stout defense like Clemson.

videos.headline: Clemson forces Virginia Tech fumble
videos.description: Clemson's Dexter Lawrence pokes the ball out of Travon McMillian's hands, and Dorian O'Daniel recovers the fumble for the Tigers.

videos.headline: Tigers score on 4th down
videos.description: Clemson goes for it on fourth-and-goal and Tavien Feaster scores from a yard out for his second touchdown of the game, giving the Tigers a 24-3 lead.

videos.headline: Virginia Tech fake field goal fails
videos.description: Virginia Tech tries to get creative on fourth-and-12, but the Clemson defense is ready, stopping the Hokies after just a one-yard gain, forcing a turnover on downs.

videos.headline: Hokies score on end-around run
videos.description: Virginia Tech scores its first touchdown of the game on an end-around to Sean Savoy from two yards out, cutting the Clemson lead to 14.

videos.headline: Tipped pass leads to Clemson pick-six score
videos.description: Dorian O'Daniel intercepts Josh Jackson's pass and takes it back 22 yards for a Tigers touchdown, giving Clemson a commanding 31-10 lead.

videos.headline: Clemson's Bryant makes great one-handed INT
videos.description: Austin Bryant reacts quickly to Josh Jackson's pass, leaping in the air and snatching it with one hand to pull off an impressive interception.

videos.headline: Jackson airs it out on 4th down for Virginia Tech TD
videos.description: On fourth-and-nine, Josh Jackson connects with Sean Savoy in the end zone for a 30-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: Swinney credits team culture for Clemson's success
videos.description: Clemson coach Dabo Swinney says he's proud of his team after a 31-17 win over No. 12 Virginia Tech, and says the Tigers' preparation is the key to their success.

videos.headline: DE Bryant breaks down his one-handed INT
videos.description: Clemson DE Austin Bryant talks about his leaping, one-handed interception, and says the Tigers defense had extra motivation after facing Virginia Tech in the ACC title game last season.

videos.headline: Clemson plays for keeps in huge road win
videos.description: Clemson goes on the road to win its eighth straight game against a ranked opponent in a dominating 31-17 effort at Virginia Tech.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Clemson plays for keeps in huge road win) 2017/09/30 ESHEET ENHL

videos.headline: Clemson the class of the ACC
videos.description: Kirk Herbstreit and Chris Fowler break down No. 2 Clemson's 31-17 victory on the road over No. 12 Virginia Tech, and discuss if any team in the ACC can beat the Tigers.

videos.headline: Bryant leads Clemson past Virginia Tech
videos.description: Kelly Bryant throws for 186 yards and a touchdown while rushing for 94 more as the No. 2 Tigers top the No. 12 Hokies 31-17.
